title: Appointments to Human Organ Transplant Board
content_text: p> The Government today (February 15) announced the appointment of Miss Ophelia Chan Chiu-ling and Miss Wong Hang-yee as the Chairman and the Vice-Chairman of the Human Organ Transplant Board respectively. At the same time, four other serving panel members of the Board have been appointed as substantive members and 11 new panel members have been appointed. All appointments will take effect from February 15, 2013, for a term of three years. Details are as follows: Appointment of new substantive members

Mr Johnny Wong Chi-keung Established under section 3 of the Human Organ Transplant Ordinance, the Board is tasked to consider applications made for the Board's prior written approval to carry out restricted organ removal and/or restricted organ transplant, to receive prescribed information about transplant operations and certificates accompanying imported organs and to perform any other functions that the Board is required or

and to perform any other functions that the Board is required or permitted to perform under the Ordinance. Under section 3A of the Ordinance, the Board consists of nine substantive members and 14 panel members from the medical, social work, legal and non-medical sectors.
